:c.:hdref refid=vars.
:etable.
:h2.Storage Classes
:p.Use these before a variable type to control how it gets stored.
:table cols='1i * 2i'.
:tcap.C Keywords: Storage Classes
:thd.
:c.:hp2.Keyword:ehp2.
:c.:hp2.Description:ehp2.
:c.:hp2.Location:ehp2.
:ethd.
:row split=yes.
:c.:pk.auto:epk.
:c.Variable is created and destroyed whenever you enter and leave the
function (this is the default and you need not type it)
:c.:hdref refid=storcls.
:row split=yes.
:c.:pk.static:epk.
:c.Make a variable's value persist across several runs of a function
:c.:hdref refid=storcls.
:row split=yes.
:c.:pk.register:epk.
:c.Confine a variable to always be in a CPU register (the compiler
does this anyways for you)
:c.:hdref refid=storcls.
:row split=yes.
:c.:pk.extern:epk.
:c.Tell the compiler that it can find a variable's location in
memory in another C file (to be resolved by the linker later)
:c.:hdref refid=storcls.
:etable.
:h2.Variable Qualifiers
:p.Put these before your storage class to control what you can do with 
the variable!
:table cols='1i * 2i'.
:tcap.C Keywords: Variable Qualifiers
:thd.
:c.:hp2.Keyword:ehp2.
